    <section>
        <title>About follow-up analysis</title>
        <para>The follow-up analysis creates a list of all data values marked for follow-up. You can
            mark a data value for follow-up in the <emphasis role="bold">Data Entry</emphasis> app
            and in the result list you get from a standard deviation outlier or minimum maximum
            <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20170106T144757+0100" comment="Verify with SME: what does this phrase mean?

In all report types, but not validation rule analysis. Could be due to one validation rule could have multiple values, the others one value that is marked." flag="done"?>outlier
            analysis.<?oxy_comment_end?></para>
    </section>
    <section>
        <title><?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20170109T140545+0100" comment="Do you analyse them in any way?

SME: open data entry, download list....

Would be good to have a link to corresponding data entry form. (JIRA)" flag="done"?>Create<?oxy_comment_end?>
            list of data values marked for
            <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20170113T085608+0100" comment="Add screenshot when validation rules have been removed from UI."?>follow<?oxy_comment_end?>-up</title>
        <orderedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>Open the <emphasis role="bold">Data Quality</emphasis> app and click <emphasis
                        role="bold">Follow-up analysis</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Select an <emphasis role="bold">Organisation unit</emphasis>.</para>
                <para>The analysis process duration depends on the amount of data that is being
                    analysed. If there are data values marked for follow-up, they will be presented
                    in a list.</para>
                <para>
                    <screenshot>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <imageobject>
                                <imagedata width="90%" align="center"
                                    fileref="resources/images/data_quality/data_quality_follow_up.png"
                                />
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </screenshot>
                </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>(Optional) Click <emphasis role="bold">Download as PDF</emphasis>, <emphasis
                        role="bold">Download as Excel</emphasis> or <emphasis role="bold">Download
                        as CSV</emphasis> to download the validation violations list in PDF, Excel
                    or CSV formats.</para>
            </listitem>
        </orderedlist>
        <para>
            <tip>
                <para>Click the star icon to remove the follow-up tag from the data value.</para>
            </tip>
        </para>
